column5: that my 16ft x 12ft car shelter blew out of my driveway, over the neighbors 6ft fence and landed intact in her maple tree.it took 4 of us to get it down.Then the wind picked it back up and threw it,and us, into the street. then all we had to do was carry it back into my driveway and re anchor it to the ground Crazy !!!!
I bet it would have been kind of funny to see you all airborne...
LOl thanks fo rthe visual!!! awesome
there's no place like home there's no place like home
You didn't get video.. shame.. shame..

why they make those things like a wing, i'll never know !!! when lift plus thrust is greater than load plus drag what happens........FLIGHT !!! THATS WHAT HAPPENS !!!  Oh well at least the boat and my truck are ok

Well you proved that theory wrong Paul... there was no thrust!!! We proved it wrong in 1989.. with a C172 in the Midland Airport tie downs. Loosened the ropes off about 4 feet and 4 of us got in for some tethered flight WITHOUT starting the engine!!!
i was thinking about you as i was being transported through the air.I shoulda asked Wayne for a quick lesson on landing,i was thinking.
